    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "(** [type_scope] must be declared and bound early on so that later reserved notations register correctly. *)",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Declare Scope type_scope.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Bind Scope type_scope with Sortclass.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n(** To reserve this notation, we must first bootstrap, and preserve the underlying [forall] notation *)\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Notation \"'forall'  x .. y , P\" := (forall x , .. (forall y, P) ..) (at level 200, x binder, y binder, right associativity).",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Reserved Notation \"'exists' x .. y , p\"\n  (at level 200, x binder, right associativity,\n   format \"'[' 'exists'  '/  ' x  ..  y ,  '/  ' p ']'\").",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n\n(** Work around bug 5569, https://coq.inria.fr/bugs/show_bug.cgi?id=5569, Warning skip-spaces-curly,parsing seems bogus *)\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Local Set Warnings \"-skip-spaces-curly\".",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n(** These are the notations whose level and associativity are imposed by Coq *)\n\n(** Notations for propositional connectives *)\n\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Reserved Notation \"x -> y\" (at level 99, right associativity, y at level 200).",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
